LoadBalancer

Now simply change

spec:
  type: LoadBalancer

Your Service becomes

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service

metadata:
  name: opentelemetry-demo-emailservice

spec:
  type: LoadBalancer

  ports:
    - port: 8080
      targetPort: 8080

  selector:
    opentelemetry.io/name: opentelemetry-demo-emailservice

Notice:

✅ No nodePort is required.

What happens now?

When Kubernetes sees

type: LoadBalancer

it asks the cloud provider.

For AWS it says

"Please create an AWS Load Balancer for me."

On AWS the flow becomes

kubectl apply
        │
        ▼
Kubernetes API Server
        │
        ▼
AWS Cloud Controller
        │
        ▼
Creates AWS Load Balancer
        │
        ▼
AWS gives a Public DNS Name

Something like

a12bc34de5678.elb.amazonaws.com
